brief run-up in mid-afternoon, but there was little followthrough, traders said.     The dollar finished at 145.25/35 yen, up from an opening 145.05/15 but below yesterday's European close of 146.00/10.     It ended at 1.5120/30 Swiss francs, against the start of 1.5130/40 and previous final 1.5180/90, and at 6.0650/700 French francs, after beginning at 6.0525/75 and ending yesterday at 6.0660/710.  REUTER ;
